<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920304-0062</DOCNO><DOCID>920304-0062.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- MCI Communications Corp.:   Concern Plans New Center   For Data, Network Services</HL><DATE>03/04/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   MCIC</CO><MS>UTILITIES (UTI)</MS><IN>LONG DISTANCE TELEPHONE PROVIDERS (LDS)TELEPHONE SYSTEMS, INCLUDING CELLULAR (TLS)</IN><RE>DISTRICT OF COLUMBIA (DC)MARYLAND (MD)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   MCI Communications Corp. plans to open an advanced dataprocessing and network management center in Perryman, Md.,early next year and plans to invest over $150 million in thefacility.   Construction of the highly automated 60,000-square-footfacility -- MCI's second-largest in the country -- isscheduled to begin in May. The long-distancetelecommunications concern, which is based in Washington,D.C., currently operates a major switching center in Perrymanthat handles over two million calls a day.</LP><TEXT>   The new center will use the latest fiber-optic technologyand provide revenue processing, billing and order processingfor MCI customers in 11 states and handle any problems in thenationwide digital network.</TEXT></DOC>